Hi Jc, let us introduce our self, we’re <a href="http://tumblr.ecoute-prolongee.com/">EcouteProlongée</a> (say it on the French way), and we recommend music for people who doesn’t know what to listen, that’s a hard job, but quite fun.

So that’s why we’re going to ask some questions, 3 actually, like we do it before with China Moses (I think you know her). So, the third question is always the same and we try to ask you « non-press-question », I mean we’re not going to ask you basic question like « Since when you play guitar » or something like that.

&nbsp;

Let’s begin?

&nbsp;

You’ve a great voice, that’s cool, you play guitar etc.. But you don’t want to play in a group? Not in a girly-band but more like <b>Noah and the Whale</b>?

Ahhh! That’s a great question! Truth be told I traveled and played in a band for 4 years before I began touring as a solo artist. It was great fun and I developed a bond a brotherhood with my band mates however now is my time to fly alone and that is okay with me.

&nbsp;

Have done some featuring with other people?

Not any major features. I’m currently working on feature for two DJ’s. One in UK and one in Germany. The idea would be something like David Guetta ft. Usher. haha

&nbsp;

What are you listening now?

I am currently listening to Michael Kiwanuka (UK), Rae Lamontagne (US), Fränk (France).  They are all amazing artists!!

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

Thx to you :)

&nbsp;

Thank you for your time! A bient<i>ôt!</i>

&nbsp;

<i>Jc</i>
